description:
&lt;p&gt;We currently have a Rapid Response Team Assistant vacancy within the Housekeeping department.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for applicants with knowledge of specialist cleaning and with the ability to use industrial cleaning equipment. This is a very physically demanding job with very high standards to be achieved. You will also need to be able to work under pressure and find challenges rewarding.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Successful applicants will provide support in keeping the environment clean and comfortable for patients as well as carrying out deep cleans on wards and departments throughout the hospital. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;37.5 hours per week, rota covers 24 hour period you will be expected to work mornings, afternoons, evening &amp; nights, including weekends &amp; bank holidays. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The rota’s will be discussed at interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post 1 - 37.5 hours per week 6 months fixed term&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alison Brant&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Facilities Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0300 131 4878&lt;/p&gt;
